block hero-content 
  section.hero-content.container 
    article.hero-copy 
      section.left 
        h1 
          span.inherit Conversations without delay. 
          span.inherit Infrastructure without shortcuts.

        p Yapper is a production-ready messaging system featuring real-time transport, modern cryptography for private communication, a Stripe-based paywall, and a reusable backend architecture that supports custom clients and external integrations.

        .btn-group.reverse
          a.btn.primary(href="/chat") Get Started
          a.btn.outline(href="https://github.com/Zain-Khoso/Yapper", target="_blank") Source Code 
      
      +hero

    article#features.features-section 
      h3 Features 

      ul.features-list 
        li.feature-card 
          h4 Stripe Paywall 
          span Subscription-based access with Stripe billing, webhooks, and server-side enforcement.

        li.feature-card 
          h4 Headless Backend
          span Use Yapper as a drop-in messaging API with your own frontend.

        li.feature-card 
          h4 Real-Time
          span Instant messaging powered by Socket.io with live delivery and presence.

        li.feature-card 
          h4 End-to-End Encryption
          span Messages secured using the X3DH key exchange—server never sees plaintext.

block content 
  main.page-contents
    section#testimonials.section.container 
      header.section-header 
        h4 Testimonials 
        h2 What do people think of Yapper?
      
      main.carousel
        button.control
          span.material-icons chevron_left

        ul.slides 
          li.slide 
            .person
              img.image(src="/assets/brand/testimonial-1.png", alt="MERN Stack Developer's Testimonial")
              
              div
                h4 Muhammad Imtiaz Hussain
                span.small MERN Stack Developer 
            
            span As a MERN-stack developer, I really liked how Yapper separates concerns—auth, messaging, encryption, and billing are all modular and easy to reason about. It feels like production code, not a demo project.

          li.slide 
            .person
              img.image(src="/assets/brand/testimonial-2.jpg", alt="Backend Engineer's Testimonial")
              
              div
                h4 Hassaan Ahmed
                span.small Backend Engineer
            
            span Socket.io is often easy to misuse, but Yapper handles real-time messaging, presence, and delivery cleanly. It's clear a lot of thought went into edge cases and state synchronization.

          li.slide 
            .person
              img.image(src="/assets/user-placeholder.png", alt="React.js Developer's Testimonial")
              
              div
                h4 Muhammad Adeen
                span.small React.js Developer 
            
            span I used Yapper's API to plug in a custom React frontend and didn't have to fight the backend at all. The endpoints are predictable, real-time events are well designed, and the docs make it easy to get started.

        button.control
          span.material-icons chevron_right

    section#pricing.section.container 
      header.section-header 
        h4 Pricing 
        h2 What other features does Yapper offer?
      
      ul.cards-list
        li.price-card 
          .header 
            h2 Gold
            
            div 
              h1 Free 
              h3 /Forever
            
            span Perfect for trying Yapper or building small projects.

          ul.perks-list 
            li.perk Real-time messaging
            li.perk End-to-end encrypted chats
            li.perk Basic API access
            li.perk Community support

          .btn-group
            a(href="/chat").btn.outline Get Started

        li.price-card 
          .header 
            h2 Diamond
            
            div 
              h1 $5 
              h3 /month
            
            span For production use and serious applications.

          ul.perks-list 
            li.perk Everything in Gold
            li.perk Priority real-time infrastructure
            li.perk Full API access for custom clients
            li.perk Stripe-powered subscription management

          .btn-group
            button.btn.primary Go Diamond

